info.description: ### **Getting Started** ## **Step 1: Fork the collection using Run in Postman** [Run in Postman](https://restless-rocket-540554.postman.co/workspace/cc63c823-b3bd-44ea-84a5-8605f332c31a/collection/24005800-0d633c4a-397e-45fa-83ac-113aa1744d37/fork?origin=tab) These are smart testing endpoints, by following this you will successfully integrate to our resources. Every endpoint has a description on the fields required to get a successful response. ## Step 2: Get your access token An access token is automatically generated using a default `client_id` and `secret` that is provided in the collection. **Note:** The `client_id` and `secret` will change when getting the resources from production endpoint. ## Step 3: Make your first API call Smart recommends starting with Policy Api. Schemecode generated from Policy Api will be used in the case of policy renewal, benefit categories and also benefits.

item.description:
# **1.1 Authorizing requests**

Before your application can access data from a given endpoint, it must first be authorized to access that resource. Smart uses an OAuth 2 based authorization server to grant Bearer tokens to clients with which you can use to access desired resources or endpoints. The bearer token is sent as an ‘HTTP Authorization’ header.

The header should have of the following format Authorization: Bearer.

# **1.1.1 End Point**

The scheme definition interface has the following properties:

• Method: POST

• Resource URL: {AUTH_URL}/oauth/token?

• Example: {AUTH_URL}/

/oauth/token?grant_type=client_credentials&client_id=XXXX&client_ secret=XXXXX
